cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.MA

The paper deals with spectrum sharing in cellular networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of stable matching game theory (cs.GT) and Q-learning (cs.MA) also suggests these categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of network resource allocation, which could fall under the category of social networks (cs.SI).
